Anyhow, ask me later on our raid performance lol, but I think it will be good (not great but good hehe).  I've not done anything major other than 1 groupers for loot.  I'm not too bad at melee at all.   I've served as maintank a few times even.  When buffed my HP's get upward to 3500 and my AC to 1050 (this is not with level 60 buffs but with Heroism, Bulwark, Symbol of Marzin, and Talsiman of Altuna).  Damage wise I would say paly like (before AA, however BST get the AA bonuses too and I plan to work on those) However with my pet out, our combined damage rocks and on the BST boards some parsing shows we combine to dish out near rogue damage.   <br>
<br>
As for class specific, all of our pet buffs and spells would be but our best class specifis spells are at level 59 and 60.  Spiritual Purity at 59 has been sweat for me.  It is a combo clarity / health regen type spell that does stack with the Clarity line.  It is a group buff to boot. <br>
<br>
At level 60 we get several pretty nice ones.  A 50% slow,  and then 2 unique ones.  One is rare, call Savagery.  I need it!  lol.  According to the spell list on EQbeastlord, for the price of a peridot, it does:<br>
<br>
Stamina +25; Atk +100; All Resists +50; Stamina Regen<br>
<br>
The other one which I already have is Spiritual Purity.  It does:<br>
<br>
Increase Total Hit Points by 250; Increase Current Hitopints by 250; Increase Dexterity by 50; Increase Strength by 67<br>
<br>
I expect and dearly hope it stacks with the talsiman line (we also get the tuna talisman) and hope but doubt it will stack with other STR and DEX buffs.  <br>
<br>
The BST's greatest strength will be solo power.  By level 60 we have the above buffs to cast on ourselves and our pets along with a very wide assortment of spells, nothing super powerful.  <br>
<br>
i.e.<br>
<br>
Spiritual Strength (the above buff I listed)<br>
Savagery (the above buff I listed)<br>
Spiritual Purity (mana &amp; hp regen)<br>
Chloroplast (HP regen)<br>
Talsiman of Altuna (HP)<br>
Shiftien Shield (AC)<br>
Sha's Advantage (50% Slow)<br>
Alacrity (40% hate)<br>
Incapacitate (AC/AGI/STR debuff)<br>
Blizzard Blast (430pt DD)<br>
Venom of the Snake (413pt DoT)<br>
Greater Healing (300pt Heal)<br>
Nulify Magic<br>
Several Resist this or that buffs<br>
Several 40ish level shammy stat buffs (STR, DEX, STA)<br>
Invisibilty/See Invis<br>
Sprit of Wolf<br>
<br>
As noted, a lot of variety but nothing super other than the first few.  Those along with cleric level heals for our pets and uber buffs for our pets make an awesome solo machine.  Once I hit 60 I'll push the limits and see just what I can solo.  <br>
<br>
